	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65496548">This inflation is the direct result of deficit spending by the government - every time monetary supply is expanded (i.e., printing money) the value of existing currency decreases. This way higher deficits result in higher inflationary pressures (i.e., things cost more, dollars exchange rate goes down). This is why many conservatives objected to the BBB, as it continued and expanded deficit spending.</div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_65496548">
